--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ubuntu Setup Script
www.arcidor.com
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

I. Description

	A shell script, used to install and configure various applications and
	settings on a freshly installed server.

	The script has five main sections:

	1. 	Setup the base installation (core system, ssh, firewall, security)
	2. 	Install system specific applications (apache, mysql, php, etc.)
	3. 	Create a backup scheme and clean the system
	
	
II. File list

	1. 	setting.sh: user configurable, customises the installation process
	2. 	core.sh: 	configuration functions for the installation
	3. 	install.sh: main executable, references all other files
	

III. Compatibility

	This tool has been configured under the following systems:
	
	1.	Ubuntu 11.04 (natty)

IV. Usage

	1. 	Download the latest version of the script:

			git://arcidor.com/ubuntu

	2. 	Navigate to the script directory
	
	3.	Configure the setting.sh file
	
	4.	Ensure that the install script is executable:
	
			chmod 700 install.sh
			
	5.	Run the script
	
			./install.sh

V. Known Issues

	None

